column2: SELECT e.idcase, strftime('%s', e.start_time) - strftime('%s', (SELECT timestamp FROM event_log WHERE idcase=e.idcase AND activity IN ('End trip', 'Declaration rejected by employee', 'Payment handled') ORDER BY timestamp LIMIT 1)) AS 'Time', (SELECT activity FROM event_log WHERE idcase=e.idcase AND activity IN ('End trip', 'Declaration rejected by employee', 'Payment handled') ORDER BY timestamp LIMIT 1) AS 'Activity' FROM (SELECT idcase, MIN(timestamp) AS start_time FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase) e
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT e.idcase, strftime('%s', e2.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.timestamp) AS 'Time', e2.activity AS 'End activity' FROM event_log e INNER JOIN ( SELECT idcase, MIN(timestamp) AS start_time FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase ) e1 ON e.idcase = e1.idcase AND e.timestamp = e1.start_time LEFT JOIN event_log e2 ON e2.idcase = e.idcase AND e2.timestamp > e.timestamp AND (e2.activity = 'End trip' OR e2.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee' OR e2.activity = 'payment handled') ORDER BY e.idcase;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled'

column2: SELECT p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity FROM event_log p INNER JOIN (SELECT idcase, MIN(timestamp) as start_time FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e ON e.idcase = p.idcase LEFT JOIN event_log x ON x.idcase = e.idcase AND x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee' LEFT JOIN event_log y ON y.idcase = e.idcase AND y.activity = 'Payment handled' INNER JOIN (SELECT idcase, MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' OR activity='Declaration rejected by employee' OR activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f ON f.idcase = e.idcase AND (f.activity = 'End trip' OR f.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee' OR f.activity = 'Payment handled')
